CREATE APPLICATION SUBDIRECTORY
step 1 - create application subdirectory
step 2 - create _Autoload.php and load class example "Examples/Api"
step 3 - create Api.php file to load structur, example "Examples/Api"
step 4 - create Subdirectory "Test"
step 5 - create _Abstract.php and Index.php file, example "Examples/Api/Example"
step 6 - other files are optional

CREATE APPLICATION
in framework is built in command "create".
it will automatically create structur for desired application/subfolder/new sub application
Abstract (template positioning, privileges and template)
Index (sub application loader)
Controller (sub application extender)
view (views)
inc (styles, scripts, etc. fro current sub application)

TEMPLATE
if route directory is below of the template directory then rename the template directory to XTemplate
also rename it in 
.htaccess
Template/_Autoload
Template/Template.php